<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="25">
The following character combination distinguishes 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. angulatus" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="angulatus">N. angulatus</taxonomicName>
from the other members of the group in the Arabian Peninsula: third mandibular tooth relatively larger and better developed; anterior clypeal lobe always conspicuously developed, convex and rounded, never with a small median triangular projection; clypeus with median longitudinal carina; pronotum anterodorsally without sharp, dentate corners; in profile mesosomal dorsum forming a single, uninterrupted flat surface without any trace of metanotal groove; petiole with very well developed node.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
